WEBVTT

00:00:00.079 --> 00:00:02.779
The film on this site's front page cost

00:00:02.779 --> 00:00:07.269
$8.26 to produce, logged line for line,

00:00:07.279 --> 00:00:09.610
and I can document every cent.

00:00:09.760 --> 00:00:12.549
Here's the problem with most portfolios:

00:00:12.679 --> 00:00:14.829
You have to take their word for it.

00:00:14.899 --> 00:00:18.269
A nice reel, big claims, no receipts.

00:00:18.379 --> 00:00:20.009
This site works differently.

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:22.699
It runs like a newsroom. Every claim links

00:00:22.699 --> 00:00:25.819
to a source. Every illustration says how

00:00:25.819 --> 00:00:28.579
it was made, and the systems that made them

00:00:28.579 --> 00:00:31.310
are public. Take the flagship,

00:00:31.459 --> 00:00:34.940
PictureLock. Step one, you hand it a plain

00:00:34.940 --> 00:00:38.219
text script. Step two, it generates the

00:00:38.219 --> 00:00:41.009
narration, the score, the sound design,

00:00:41.039 --> 00:00:43.979
the shots, the captions, even a Spanish

00:00:43.979 --> 00:00:47.289
dub. Incluso un doblaje al español.

00:00:47.439 --> 00:00:50.219
Step three, it logs every call,

00:00:50.219 --> 00:00:53.859
model, and cost to a run manifest and prints

00:00:53.859 --> 00:00:57.750
the receipt. That's how a 53-second film

00:00:57.750 --> 00:01:01.669
lands at $8.26, and the same gates that

00:01:01.669 --> 00:01:03.979
checked it check this whole site.

00:01:04.409 --> 00:01:06.599
Voice scoring, code review,

00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:09.350
resolution audits, public,

00:01:09.350 --> 00:01:12.909
dated, zero open flags. Even this voice

00:01:12.909 --> 00:01:16.500
is synthetic, cloned from me with my consent.

00:01:16.530 --> 00:01:19.450
I'm Mitchell. If you're hiring for AI production

00:01:19.450 --> 00:01:22.109
work, there's a 12-minute path from start

00:01:22.109 --> 00:01:24.749
to verdict. So look around,

00:01:24.749 --> 00:01:26.999
check the receipts, and when you're ready,

00:01:27.049 --> 00:01:28.039
come find me.
